ome to reassess 1980s progressive politics, despite its undeniable electoral failures. With this in mind, the contributors offer ground-breaking research and penetrating arguments about the strange death of Labour Britain.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aElectronic books. 0aSocialismzGreat BritainxHistoryy20th century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Process / Political Parties.2bisacsh  aBermondsey by-election.  aBrexit referendum.  aConservative Government.  aGreater London Council.  aLiverpool City Council.  aMikhail Gorbachev.  aNeil Kinnock.  aNew Labour Party.  aRace Today Collective.  aThatcherism.  aTony Benn.  ablack liberation.  ablack radicals.  acentral government rate-capping.  acontinental social democracy.  aleft politics.  amass deindustrialisation.  aminers' strike.  anational investment bank.  astate intervention.1 aBloomfield, Paul, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBunce, Robin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCallaghan, John, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCarr, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDavis, Jonathan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aFarr, Martin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoannou, Maroula, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcWilliam, Rohan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMcWilliam, Rohan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aPye, Neil, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShaw, Eric, econtributor.4ctb4https://i